device.MRISafety_status: Labeling does not contain MRI Safety Information

gmdn.gmdn_ptdefinition:
A small, implantable sheet of firm material that
					is attached with screws to fractured craniofacial bone (including
					the maxilla and/or mandible), to bridge and stabilize the fracture
					gap, and shield the site from stress as the bone heals; the
					material cannot be chemically degraded or absorbed by natural body
					processes [includes implant grade metal such as surgical steel,
					titanium alloy, or carbon fibre]. The device may also be used for
					craniofacial reconstructive procedures (e.g., to treat congenital
					malformations), endobrow fixation, or craniotomy flap fixation.
